chool Parent Guide Boarding School Packing Lists Student Discount Programs Local Shopping Resources This comprehensive guide provides the tactical, step-by-step approach you need to successfully transition from summer camp to boarding school preparation. The detailed tables, cost analysis, and optimization strategies will help you make informed decisions while staying within budget and timeline constraints. Your summer camp packing list provides an excellent foundation - now it's time to build upon it strategically for the full boarding school experience at Grier School. do parents bri g linens and bedding to school Yes, parents typically bring linens and bedding to boarding school, and this is actually one of the most important differences between summer camp and boarding school preparation. Let me search for specific information about bedding requirements. Using Tool | Search boarding school bedding linens parents bring twin XL sheets requirements View Using Tool | Search \"Grier School\" bedding requirements what to bring dorm room View Let me search for more specific information about what boarding schools typically provide versus what parents need to bring. Using Tool | Search boarding school what does school provide vs what parents bring bedding furniture View Using Tool | Search boarding school dorm room furnished mattress sheets pillows what to bring View Now let me create a comprehensive table that clearly shows what boarding schools provide versus what parents need to bring, specifically for bedding and linens. Using Tool | Create Sheet & Set Header View Boarding School Bedding and Linens: What's Provided vs What to Bring Click to open Continue in AI Sheets Mode YES - Parents Bring ALL Linens and Bedding to Boarding School Critical Answer: What Schools Provide vs What Parents Bring Based on my research of boarding school standards, including multiple schools' packing lists, here's the definitive breakdown: 🏫 SCHOOL PROVIDES: Bed frame (Twin XL size) Mattress (basic Twin XL) Desk and chair Dresser (4-5 drawers) Closet/wardrobe space Basic room utilities 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 PARENTS MUST BRING: ALL bedding and linens ALL personal comfort items ALL storage solutions ALL decorative items Essential Bedding Shopping List for Boarding School IMMEDIATE PRIORITY (Must Have) Item\tQuantity\tSize\tCost Estimate Twin XL Fitted Sheets\t2 sets\t39\" x 80\"\t$15-40 each Twin XL Flat Sheets\t2 sets\t39\" x 80\"\t$15-40 each Pillows\t2\tStandard 20\" x 26\"\t$20-60 each Pillowcases\t4\tStandard 20\" x 30\"\t$10-25 per set Comforter/Duvet\t1 main + 1 backup\tTwin XL 68\" x 90\"\t$40-150 each Bath Towels\t3-4\tStandard 27\" x 52\"\t$15-30 each Total Essential Bedding Cost: $200-500 RECOMMENDED ADDITIONS Item\tPurpose\tCost Estimate Mattress Topper\tComfort upgrade\t$50-150 Mattress Protector\tHygiene/protection\t$15-40 Extra Blankets\tWarmth/comfort\t$20-50 each Throw Pillows\tRoom personality\t$15-30 each Key Differences from Your Summer Camp List From Your Summer Camp Packing List: ✅ Sleeping bag → UPGRADE TO: Twin XL sheet sets + comforter ✅ Purple pillow → KEEP: Plus add pillowcases and backup pillow ✅ Pillowcase → EXPAND TO: 4 pillowcases (2 sets) ✅ Fitted sheet → UPGRADE TO: Twin XL fitted sheets (2 sets) ✅ Flat sheet → UPGRADE TO: Twin XL flat sheets (2 sets) ✅ Towels (3) → ORGANIZE: Bath towels + hand towels + washcloths Critical Sizing Note: Summer camp beds: Usually regular Twin (39\" x 75\") Boarding school beds: Almost always Twin XL (39\" x 80\") Your current sheets may be too short! Tactical Shopping Strategy Phase 1: Size Verification (Week 1) Contact Grier School to confirm exact mattress dimensions Measure your current sheets to verify size compatibility Create specific shopping list with exact measurements Phase 2: Strategic Purchasing (Week 2-3) Shop end-of-season sales (August for back-to-school) Buy quality basics first (sheets, pillows, towels) Consider bundled sets for cost savings Phase 3: Comfort Upgrades (Week 4-5) Add mattress topper if budget allows Purchase decorative items for personalization Buy storage solutions for organization Cost Optimization Tips Smart Shopping Strategies: Target/Walmart: Basic sheets and towels ($100-200 total) Amazon: Bundled bedding sets with good reviews Bed Bath & Beyond: Quality comforters with college discounts Costco: Bulk towels and storage containers Quality Investment Priority: Sheets (daily use - invest in comfort) Mattress topper (affects sleep quality) Towels (durability matters) Comforter (warmth and comfort) Common Boarding School Bedding Mistakes to Avoid ❌ Buying regular Twin size instead of Twin XL ❌ Only bringing one set of sheets (laundry delays) ❌ Forgetting mattress protector (hygiene issues) ❌ Overspending on decorative items before basics ❌ Not checking school-specific restrictions on bedding Final Recommendations Immediate Action Items: Confirm bed size with Grier School admissions Budget $300-600 for complete bedding setup Start shopping now for best selection and prices Keep receipts for exchanges/returns Long-term Strategy: Rotate bedding to extend life Bring repair kit for minor tears Plan mid-year refresh if needed Consider seasonal bedding for comfort Bottom Line: Your summer camp list covers about 60% of the bedding needs. You'll need to upgrade sizing, add backup sets, and include additional comfort items for the full academic year at boarding school. The good news? You have a solid foundation to build upon - just need to scale up for the longer stay and different bed size requirements. i have 2 sets of nee twin XL full bedding and linens. make a detailed categorized checklist of what im still needing to buy Perfect! Since you already have 2 sets of Twin XL bedding, let me create a detailed categorized checklist of what you still need to buy for Grier boarding school, building on your summer camp list and existing bedding. Using Tool | Create Sheet & Set Header View Still Needed for Grier Boarding School - Detailed Shoppin